// Harper Journal rq tob2 fighter
COPY ~golden_horse/itm/rqlett1.itm~ ~override/rqlett1.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Journal~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Journal~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~This is journal of Harper he mostly writes about himself and his actions. For example last entry.
"We shall be facing Bhaalspawn soon but I am worried. I heard he killed like three dozens of our men. I wish I could talk to someone about my concers but anyone I talk to is dismissive of anything I say."~

// Jaheira letter tob1 encounter
COPY ~golden_horse/itm/rqlettj2.itm~ ~override/rqlettj2.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Letter~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Letter~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~This small letter apparently for delivery by courier pigeon states:
"I am under pressure from Elminster to cease my support for you do not worry my cell will continue to support you."~


// Jaheira letter tob1 encounter
COPY ~golden_horse/itm/rqlettj3.itm~ ~override/rqlettj3.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Letter~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Letter~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~Jaheira for your task of slaying Bhaalspawn I am sending you the best men that I could find. They are quite evil folk but they fight well and you did not request morally sound warriors.
Try not to die this time.

K.~

// Jaheira letter tob1 encounter
COPY ~golden_horse/itm/rqlettj.itm~ ~override/rqlettj.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Scroll~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Scroll~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~What is happening to you Jaheira? I used to remember you as someone very reasonable and now you lie to your own! This pretending that you lost your wits to gain sympathy with Harpers?! What has gotten into you?! How much of our assets will be destroyed meaninglessly if you will continue in this?! Have you thought of that?
You may have many supporters right now but that does not make you above Harper code.

I implore you to stop this foolish revenge and seek me out.

E.

It seems that Jaheira has wrote her reply right below. Though there are many scratched out words as if Jaheira was unsure how to respond.
You can make out few words like "tested" "Amel" "more" and "enemy"

I don't do this because of petty revenge and you know this. Wish you would understand <CHARNAME> must be punished for his wanton murder of Those Who Harp.~

// Jaheira letter tob3 encounter
COPY ~golden_horse/itm/rqlettj4.itm~ ~override/rqlettj4.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Letter~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Letter~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~This small letter apparently for delivery by courier pigeon states:
End justifies means this not our way remember that Jaheira. You made fool out of me and that is not forgivable your ruse is finished. Elminster told me who your allies are. What has happened to you Jaheira? Did those resurrections damaged your sanity?.
I have enchanted your allies so that no one will be suspicious but this is your last chance no one will resurrect you now remember that.
To summon them hold this letter in your hand think of command word "Tzrhglosugligh"~

// Thacher journal
COPY ~golden_horse/itm/rqjoutha.itm~ ~override/rqjoutha.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Thacher's Journal~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Thacher's Journal~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~Here is a corrected version of your journal entries with improved grammar and clarity, avoiding the use of em dashes:

This journal writer mainly talks about himself and his mercantile exploits, but the later entries are much more interesting:

Today my lower back hurt so much... Keeping my mind occupied is one of the more useful ways to keep my mind off the pain. I guess my old and aching body is not much for this world.

I spoke to my old friend Ztrazle, who ordered magic potions from an alchemist in Moonsea. He made some really wild claims about reversing his aging and becoming more resistant to disease. I must say that my friend is in much better spirits than I have ever observed, and he looks younger compared to what I recall. I might make an order myself—what do I have to lose, anyway?

The potion has arrived, but the alchemist's accompanying letter has some dire warnings against quaffing it if the recipient's soul is weak. Whatever that means, only Demogorgon knows.

That damnable priest cost me 500 gold pieces and could not deliver anything meaningful. I strongly suspect that I overpaid him and he strung me along to make me return for further consultations. However, speaking to some acolytes proved to be more fruitful, though their words were not encouraging, to say the least.

Minus another 200 gold, and I am told that my soul is really weak. Perhaps I was trying to tackle it the wrong way. Rereading the alchemist's note, I noticed that before this potion is consumed, one has to put a tiny amount of blood onto the crate to trigger its soul merging. I assume it means unlocking its power. Which means I should just get someone who is really powerful and get him to bleed onto the crate.

I have arrived at Amkethran, as I have heard a rumor that someone with Bhaal's blood is in town. Could it be that Balthazar is a Child of Bhaal? Speaking to the monks revealed it is highly likely, but I cannot just visit the fortress and demand his blood. Perhaps he would be amenable to trade. I have purchased a powerful shield. Perhaps in exchange for my artifact, he would be willing to part with a tiny portion of his soul.

Curses! The meeting with the monks did not go well, but when I returned, I was accosted by someone named Illasera, claiming to be a Child of Bhaal. She refused outright my proposal but had a valid counter-proposal. I sure hope this will work.

What sort of sorcery she will be using to "return with the face of Gorion's Ward"? I do not want to know, but as long as she will let me gather enough blood, I don't care.
~

// Letter to Prangl
COPY ~golden_horse/itm/rqletpra.itm~ ~override/rqletpra.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Letter~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Letter~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~You know Revan so I am sending you as negotiator. You are to convince Revan to become our informant. If he turns hostile to our proposals you know what to do.~

